author: Inside Edition
description: Travis Kelce popped the question to Taylor Swift in a garden filled with flowers. The pair posted the joint announcement on social media. The ring is known as an "Old Mine Brilliant Cut," and it is set in a gold band. The announcement came 13 days after Swift's PDA-filled appearance on the Kelce brothers' "New Heights" podcast. The couple started dating in July 2023. Swift quickly became a staple at Kansas City Chiefs games.
title: Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce Announce Engagement

author: Inside Edition
description: Principal Zac Bauermeister, or Dr. B. as the kids call him, was dubbed the most popular principal in America this year after a video went viral with over 380 million views. Inside Edition was at Providence Elementary School in Lancaster, Pennsylvania, as Dr. B greeted kids for the first day of school. Dr. B's teachers know he's making a difference with the kids. "It's the little things that make a big difference, just connecting with kids. Something as small as a fist bump," Dr. B says.
title: 'Most Popular Principal' Greets Kids for 1st Day of School

author: Inside Edition
description: Frieda Birnbaum, who gained notoriety in 2007 after giving birth to her twin boys at the age of 60, sent her kids off to college. The twins are now 18 and mom is 78. Many doubted she would be able to raise twin boys in her senior years. Looking back, Josh and Jaret say it was really a normal upbringing. Inside Edition was there when the twins' mom and dad, now 81, helped Josh move into his dorm at Stevens Institute of Technology. Jaret is headed off to Northeastern University.
title: Twin Boys of America's 'Grannymom' Head Off to College

author: Inside Edition
description: Bodycam video shows the dad who police say brutally murdered his three young daughters, then vanished. Travis Decker, 32, was questioned by police after he was involved in a fender bender. Seventy-two hours later, Decker allegedly murdered his children Paityn, Evelyn, and Olivia at a remote campsite in Washington State's Wenatchee National Forest. Three months after the slaying, authorities are stepping up the search, assigning 100 FBI agents to it.
title: Authorities Step Up Search for Alleged Murderer Travis Decker

author: Inside Edition
description: Cardi B is being sued by a security guard who claims the rapper "cut her left cheek with a three-inch fingernail." The alleged incident happened when Cardi B was pregnant in 2018 and leaving her doctor's office. The singer claims security guard Emani Ellis tried to record a cell phone video of her, and says when she asked Ellis to stop, the security guard began "screaming at her" and "taking swings." Cardi B denied there was any physical contact.
title: Security Guard Sues Cardi B for Allegedly Scratching Her Cheek

author: Inside Edition
description: Bruce Willis' wife, Emma Heming Willis, is opening up about the moment she noticed a change in her husband. The legendary actor, best known for the Die-Hard films, developed a stutter, which he also had in childhood. A brain scan revealed Bruse was suffering from frontotemporal dementia. Emma told ABC's Diane Sawyer the doctors said there was nothing that could be done, and there was no cure. Inside Edition spoke with neurologist Dr. Jinsy Andrews.
title: Bruce Willis' Wife Opens Up About Actor's Health

description: According to the FBI's Jackson office, agents are investigating a man they say worked as a gymnastics coach in Mississippi, Louisiana and Iowa.
title: FBI Seeks Info on Accused Gymnastics Coach #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: It's been traveling through space for billions of years, not too far from Earth. But rather than fear this asteroid, scientists say they wanted to get to know it better. In 2020, a NASA spacecraft landed on this carbon-rich rock, named Bennu, and collected more than 100 samples. Scientists believe it could help them unlock some long-held secrets of space. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Particles From Asteroid Older Than Solar System Unlock Secrets of Space
